file.name: nytimes.com-geo_api-1.0.0-swagger.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.0 info: description: > The Geographic API extends the Semantic API, using a linked data approach to enhance location concepts used in The New York Times' controlled vocabulary and data resources which combine them with the GeoNames database, an authoritative and free to use database of global geographical places, names and features. termsOfService: http://developer.nytimes.com/tou title: Geographic version: 1.0.0 x-apiClientRegistration: url: http://developer.nytimes.com/signup x-apisguru-categories: - media - open_data x-logo: url: https://static01.nyt.com/images/icons/t_logo_291_black.png x-origin: - format: swagger url: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/NYTimes/public_api_specs/master/geo_api/geo_api_v2.json version: "2.0" x-providerName: nytimes.com x-serviceName: geo_api externalDocs: url: http://developer.nytimes.com/ security: - apikey: [] paths: /query.json: get: description: Geographic API parameters: - description: A displayable name for the specified place. in: query name: name required: false schema: type: string - description: | The latitude of the specified place. in: query name: latitude schema: type: string - description: The longitude of the specified place. in: query name: longitude schema: type: string - description: The elevation of the specified place, in meters. in: query name: elevation required: false schema: type: integer - description: Along with ne, forms a bounded box using the longitude and latitude coordinates specified as the southwest corner. The search results are limited to the resulting box. Two float values, separated by a comma `latitude,longitude`
The ne parameter is required to use this parameter. in: query name: sw required: false schema: type: string - description: > Search keywords to perform a text search on the fields: web_description, event_name and venue_name. 'AND' searches can be performed by wrapping query terms in quotes. If you do not specify a query, all results will be returned. in: query name: query required: false schema: type: string - description: > Filters search results based on the facets provided. For more information on the values you can filter on, see Facets. in: query name: filter required: false schema: type: string - description: Start date to end date in the following format- YYYY-MM-DD:YYYY-MM-DD in: query name: date_range required: false schema: type: string - description: When facets is set to 1, a count of all facets will be included in the response. in: query name: facets schema: type: integer enum: - 0 - 1 default: 0 - description: > Sorts your results on the fields specified.
`sort_value1+[asc | desc],sort_value2+[asc|desc],[...]`
Appending +asc to a facet or response will sort results on that value in ascending order. Appending +desc to a facet or response will sort results in descending order. You can sort on multiple fields. You can sort on any facet. For the list of responses you can sort on, see the Sortable Field column in the Response table.

If you are doing a spatial search with the ll parameter, you can also sort by the distance from the center of the search: dist+[asc | desc]
**Note:** either +asc or +desc is required when using the sort parameter. in: query name: sort schema: type: string - description: Limits the number of results returned in: query name: limit schema: type: integer default: 20 - description: Sets the starting point of the result set in: query name: offset schema: type: integer default: 0 responses: "200": description: An array of events content: application/json: schema: properties: results: items: $ref: "#/components/schemas/Event" type: array type: object summary: Geographic API tags: - Events servers: - url: http://api.nytimes.com/svc/semantic/v2/geocodes - url: https://api.nytimes.com/svc/semantic/v2/geocodes components: securitySchemes: apikey: in: query name: api-key type: apiKey schemas: Event: properties: city: type: string critic_name: type: string event_detail_url: type: string event_id: type: integer event_name: type: string event_schedule_id: type: integer festival: type: boolean film_rating: type: boolean free: type: boolean kid_friendly: type: boolean last_chance: type: boolean last_modified: type: string long_running_show: type: boolean previews_and_openings: type: boolean recur_days: items: type: string type: array recurring_start_date: type: string state: type: string times_pick: type: boolean web_description: type: string type: object
